SIMPLE: flaming
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flaming
<hw>Flam"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Emitting
flames; afire; blazing; consuming; illuminating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of the color of flame; high-colored; brilliant;
dazzling.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧In <xex>flaming</xex> yellow bright.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Ardent; passionate; burning with zeal; irrepressibly
earnest; <as>as, a <ex>flaming</ex> proclamation or
harangue</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flamingly</ent>⟦br⟧
